  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\ngo-ethereum version: v1.9.25\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nReceive function should increment totalSupply variable\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\n\r\nDoes not increment variable.\r\n\r\n#### Overview\r\n\r\nI'm testing out [this contract](https://github.com/bonedaddy/geth-pending-state-test/blob/master/contracts/test.sol) using the simulated backend. I'm testing it [with this golang code](https://github.com/bonedaddy/geth-pending-state-test/blob/master/main.go). The TotalSupply variable should be set and incremented to 2, but it does not, as per the following output:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2021/01/30 01:34:39 gas used by deployment transaction:  147403 [test contract deployment]\r\n2021/01/30 01:34:39 gas used by transaction:  42265 []\r\n2021/01/30 01:34:39 gas used by transaction:  21000 [sendeth 0xd2d50a33c3c6bfed86333c000c6d1ffb6e40eb0c0fbd0630eef75b04ecd9c527]\r\n2021/01/30 01:34:39 error: supply should be 2\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Reproduction steps:\r\n\r\n```shell\r\n$> git clone https://github.com/bonedaddy/geth-pending-state-test.git\r\n$> cd geth-pending-state-test\r\n$> go mod download\r\n$> go build\r\n$> ./geth-pending-state-test\r\n```",
